Package: ENSEMBLE
Title: An Enhancer Set Enrichment Method with Biological Explanations
Version: 2.2.0
Authors@R:
    person("Laizhi", "Zhang", , "laz64@pitt.edu", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-4489-7038"))
Description: Provides enhancer-centric preprocessing, differential enhancer
    expression (DEE), set enrichment (ESEA/GSEA), and visualization utilities
    for perturbation studies. Includes scripts for generating enhancer and
    gene matrices from FASTQ files plus a Python evidence-classifier agent
    (Anthropic Claude Opus 4.5 for verdict classification and Sonnet 4.5
    for narrative generation) under local_agent/ that classifies GSEA
    pathway themes against enhancer-program helpers as SUPPORTED, PARTIAL,
    or GENE_LEVEL_ONLY, with multi-helper convergent evidence,
    post-clustering redundancy merger, 3-run consensus reproducibility,
    and a mini-thesis report writer. eORA for trait-associated SNP
    enrichment analysis is also included.
